		<div class="story-heads">
		<h1>Daniel Mason, Rachel Aviv, Emeline Atwood and more: 21 new books out today!</h1>
			</div>
	</div>
										<div class="byline-date">
					<span class="byline"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/juliahass/"  title="Julia Hass">Julia Hass</a></span>
					<span class="hr"></span>
					<span class="date">July 7, 2026</span>
				</div>
						<div class="story-body">
								<p style="text-align: left;">It&#8217;s July, and it&#8217;s time to be absolutely inundated with summer novels. This week, we&#8217;re treated to the new book by <em>North Woods</em> author Daniel Mason, <em>Country People</em>, the hotly anticipated debut novel by Emeline Atwood, <em>A Real Animal</em>, and the sequel to Irvine Welsh&#8217;s <em>Trainspotting, Men in Love</em>. And so, so many more. Read on for the full list below, and welcome to a hot and literary summer!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;">*</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264643" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/daniel-mason-country-people/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Daniel-Mason-Country-People.jpg" data-orig-size="1011,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Daniel Mason, Country People" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Daniel-Mason-Country-People-690x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264643" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Daniel-Mason-Country-People-202x300.jpg" alt="Daniel Mason, Country People" width="202" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Daniel-Mason-Country-People-202x300.jpg 202w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Daniel-Mason-Country-People-690x1024.jpg 690w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Daniel-Mason-Country-People-768x1139.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Daniel-Mason-Country-People-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Daniel-Mason-Country-People-34x50.jpg 34w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Daniel-Mason-Country-People.jpg 1011w" sizes="(max-width: 202px) 100vw, 202px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Daniel Mason, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9798217197453" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Country People</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Random House)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“Wonderful—full of joy—and exactly the kind of reading experience we could all do with right now &#8230; The book of the summer.”<br />
<em>–</em>Mick Herron</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264637" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/rachel-aviv-you-wont-get-free-of-it/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rachel-Aviv-You-Wont-Get-Free-of-It-.jpg" data-orig-size="343,522" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Rachel Aviv, You Won&amp;#8217;t Get Free of It-" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rachel-Aviv-You-Wont-Get-Free-of-It-.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264637" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rachel-Aviv-You-Wont-Get-Free-of-It--197x300.jpg" alt="Rachel Aviv, You Won't Get Free of It:" width="197" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rachel-Aviv-You-Wont-Get-Free-of-It--197x300.jpg 197w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rachel-Aviv-You-Wont-Get-Free-of-It--39x60.jpg 39w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rachel-Aviv-You-Wont-Get-Free-of-It--33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Rachel-Aviv-You-Wont-Get-Free-of-It-.jpg 343w" sizes="(max-width: 197px) 100vw, 197px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Rachel Aviv, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780525657057" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>You Won&#8217;t Get Free of It: Stories of Mothers and Daughters</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Knopf)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Both intellectually and empathetically astute, probing the uneasy complexity of a defining relationship dynamic.”<br />
<em>–Kirkus</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264641" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/emeline-atwood-a-real-animal/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emeline-Atwood-A-Real-Animal.jpg" data-orig-size="993,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Emeline Atwood, A Real Animal" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emeline-Atwood-A-Real-Animal-678x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264641" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emeline-Atwood-A-Real-Animal-199x300.jpg" alt="Emeline Atwood, A Real Animal" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emeline-Atwood-A-Real-Animal-199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emeline-Atwood-A-Real-Animal-678x1024.jpg 678w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emeline-Atwood-A-Real-Animal-768x1160.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emeline-Atwood-A-Real-Animal-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emeline-Atwood-A-Real-Animal-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/Emeline-Atwood-A-Real-Animal.jpg 993w" sizes="(max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Emeline Atwood, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781646222964" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Real Animal</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Catapult)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Emeline Atwood&#8217;s <i>A Real Animal</i> is a strange and astonishing and entirely original book, full of darkness shot through with light, wild and tender.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Elizabeth McCracken</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="264636" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/lit-hubs-most-anticipated-books-of-2026/david-thomson-a-sudden-flicker-of-light/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Thomson-A-Sudden-Flicker-of-Light-.jpg" data-orig-size="994,1500" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="David Thomson, A Sudden Flicker of Light-" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Thomson-A-Sudden-Flicker-of-Light--679x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-264636" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Thomson-A-Sudden-Flicker-of-Light--199x300.jpg" alt="David Thomson, A Sudden Flicker of Light:" width="199" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Thomson-A-Sudden-Flicker-of-Light--199x300.jpg 199w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Thomson-A-Sudden-Flicker-of-Light--679x1024.jpg 679w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Thomson-A-Sudden-Flicker-of-Light--768x1159.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Thomson-A-Sudden-Flicker-of-Light--40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Thomson-A-Sudden-Flicker-of-Light--33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/12/David-Thomson-A-Sudden-Flicker-of-Light-.jpg 994w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 199px) 100vw, 199px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>David Thomson, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9781668205730" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>A Sudden Flicker of Light: A Revisionist History of Movies</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Simon and Schuster)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">“Thomson is considered a preeminent film critic and historian, and this absolutely essential, indispensable book shows us why.”<br />
<em>–Booklist</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="273821" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/getting-to-know-santa-cruz-county-street-by-street-path-by-path/scavenging-beauty/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/scavenging-beauty.jpeg" data-orig-size="286,450" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="scavenging beauty" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/scavenging-beauty.jpeg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-273821" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/scavenging-beauty-191x300.jpeg" alt="" width="191" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/scavenging-beauty-191x300.jpeg 191w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/scavenging-beauty-38x60.jpeg 38w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/scavenging-beauty-32x50.jpeg 32w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/scavenging-beauty.jpeg 286w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 191px) 100vw, 191px" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Angelica Glass, <a href="https://bookshop.org/a/40/9780593855348" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="external"><em>Scavenging Beauty: A Memoir in Walks</em></a></strong><br />
<strong>(Riverhead)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;This is beautiful nature writing, coupled with depth and insight into trauma, forgiveness and especially love. This book inspires as it charms.&#8221;<br />
<em>–</em>Anne Lamott</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="273958" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/daniel-mason-rachel-aviv-emeline-atwood-and-more-21-new-books-out-today/helpless-9781668062302_hr/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr.jpg" data-orig-size="1400,2125" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Helpless, Jessica Knoll" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr-675x1024.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-273958" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr-198x300.jpg" alt="Helpless, Jessica Knoll" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr-675x1024.jpg 675w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr-768x1166.jpg 768w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr-1012x1536.jpg 1012w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr-1349x2048.jpg 1349w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/helpless-9781668062302_hr.jpg 1400w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></p>
