<strong>(Scribner)</strong></p>
<p style="text-align: center;">&#8220;Knoll&#8217;s twisty tale of psychological suspense, with its exploration of a nuanced relationship with elements of submission and control, will get readers talking.”<br />
<em>–Booklist</em></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-attachment-id="273960" data-permalink="https://lithub.com/daniel-mason-rachel-aviv-emeline-atwood-and-more-21-new-books-out-today/81kjejd8jwl-_ac_uf10001000_ql80_/" data-orig-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/81kJejD8JWL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" data-orig-size="659,1000" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="Exit Stalin, Mark B Smith" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-large-file="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/81kJejD8JWL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-273960" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/81kJejD8JWL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-198x300.jpg" alt="Exit Stalin, Mark B Smith" width="198" height="300" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/81kJejD8JWL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-198x300.jpg 198w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/81kJejD8JWL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-40x60.jpg 40w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/81kJejD8JWL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-33x50.jpg 33w, https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/06/81kJejD8JWL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg 659w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 198px) 100vw, 198px" /></p>
